obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (70798)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Laws repealed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70798&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `Regulation X. 1818 (relating to collection of the public revenue from proprietors`
  line `and farmers of land in the District of Cuttack, &c) is hereby repealed; and from the date of the passing of`
  line `this law, Act I of 1845 (regarding sales of land for arrears of revenue), except in so far as it repeals other`
  line `laws, and except in regard to sales made or advertised, to arrears and other demands realizable, and to`
  line `suits commenced and acts done, under authority thereof—shall cease to have effect in the Lower`
  line `Provinces of Bengal.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (70799)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `What is an arrear of revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70799&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `If the whole or a portion of a kist or instalment of any month of`
  line `the era according to which the settlement and kistbundee of any mehal have been regulated, be unpaid on`
  line `the first of the following month of such era, the sum so remaining unpaid shall be considered an arrear of`
  line revenue.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (70800)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Latest day of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70800&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Upon the promulgation of this Act, the Board of Revenue at Calcutta`
  line `shall determine upon what dates all arrears of revenue and all demands which, by the Regulations and`
  line `Acts in force, are directed to be realized in the same manner as arrears of revenue, shall be paid up in each`
  line `district under their jurisdiction, in default of which payment the estates ill arrear in those districts, except`
  line `as hereinafter provided, shall be sold at public auction to the highest bidder. And the said Board shall give`
  line `notice of the dates so fixed in the official Gazette, and shall direct corresponding publication to be made,`
  line `as far as regards each district in the language of that district, in the Office of the Collector or other Officer`
  line `duly authorized to hold sales under this Act, in the Courts of the Judge, Magistrate, (or Joint Magistrate,`
  line `as the case may be,) and Moonsiffs, and at every Thannah station of that district; and the dates so fixed`
  line `shall not be changed except by the said Board by advertisement and notification, in the manner above`
  line `described, to be issued at least three months before the close of the official year preceding that in which`
  line `the new date is, or dates are, to take effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (70801)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `In Sylhet, personal property of defaulters may in the first instance be distrained and sold.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70801&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Provided that in the district of Sylhet, the Collector may be authorized by the Board of Revenue to`
  line `proceed in the first instance by the distress and sale of the personal property of defaulters, instead of by`
  line `the sale of their estates.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (70802)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Proviso in the case of certain descriptions of arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70802&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Provided always that no estate, and no`
  line `share or interest in any estate, shall be sold for the recovery of arrears or demands of the descriptions`
  line `mentioned below, otherwise than after a notification in the language of the district specifying the nature`
  line `and amount of the arrear or demand, and the latest date on which payment thereof shall be received, shall`
  line `have been affixed for a period of not less than fifteen clear days preceding the date fixed for payment`
  line `according to Section III of this Act, in the Office of the Collector or other Officer duly authorized to hold`
  line `sales under this Act, in the Court of the Judge within whose jurisdiction the land advertised lies, and in`
  line `the Moonsiff’s Court and Police thannah of the division in which the estate or share of an estate to which`
  line `the notification relates is situated; or is the estate or share of an estate be situated within the jurisdiction of`
  line `more than one Moonsiff’s Court or Police Thannah, in some one or more of such Courts or Thannas ; and`
  line `also at the cutcherry of the malgoozar or owner of the estate or share of an estate, or at some conspicuous`
  line `place upon the estate or share of an estate, the same to be certified by the peon or other person employed`
  line `for the purpose.`
  line
  line `First. Arrears other than those of the current year, or of the year immediately preceding.`
  line
  line `Secondly. Arrears due on account of estates other than that to be sold.`
  line
  line `Thirdly. Arrears of estates under attachment by order of any judicial authority, or managed by the`
  line `Collector in accordance with such order.`
  line
  line `Fourthly. Arrears due on account of tuccavee, poolbundee, or other demands not being land revenue,`
  line `but recoverable by the same process as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (70803)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Notifications of sale to be issued, and no tender after latest day of payment to stop the sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70803&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Collector or other Officer duly authorized to hold sales under this Act shall, as soon as`
  line `possible after the latest day of payment fixed in the manner prescribed in Section III of this Act, issue`
  line `notifications in the language of the district, to be affixed in his own Office and in the Court of the Judge`
  line `of the district, specifying the estates or shares of estates which will be sold as aforesaid, and the day on`
  line `which the sale of the same will commence, which day shall not be less than fifteen or more than thirty`
  line `clear days from the date of affixing the notification in the Office of the Collector or other Officer as`
  line `aforesaid. And if the Government revenue of any estate or share: of an estate to be sold, exceed the sum`
  line `of five hundred Rupees, a notification of the sale of such estate or share of an estate shall be published in`
  line `the official Gazette. Except as hereinafter provided, all estates or shares of estates so specific shall, on the`
  line `day notified for sale, or on the day or days following, be put up to public auction by and in the presence of`
  line `the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid, and shall be sold to the highest bidder. And no payment, or`
  line `tender of payment, made after sunset of the said latest day of payment, shall bar or interfere with the sale,`
  line `either at the time of sale or after its conclusion.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (70804)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Notice to ryots, &.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70804&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Whenever an estate or share of an estate is notified for sale as provided by`
  line `Section VI of this Act, the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid shall affix a proclamation in the`
  line `language of the district, in his own Office, and as soon thereafter as may be in the Moonsiffs' Courts and`
  line `Police Thannahs within which the estate or share of an estate, or any part of it, is situated, and also at the`
  line `cutcherry of the malgoozar or the owner of the estate or share of an estate, or at some conspicuous place`
  line `upon the estate or share of an estate, forbidding the ryots and under tenants to pay to the defaulting`
  line `proprietor any rent which has fallen due after the day fixed for the last day of payment, on pain of not`
  line `being entitled to credit in their accounts with the purchaser for any sums so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (70805)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Claims against Government held by a defaulter not to invalidate a sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70805&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No claim to`
  line `abatement or remission of revenue, unless the same shall have been allowed by the authority of`
  line `Government, and no private demand or cause of action whatever, held or supposed to be held by any`
  line `defaulter against Government, shall bar or render void or voidable a sale under this Act; nor shall the plea`
  line `that money belonging to the defaulter, and sufficient to pay the arrear of revenue due, was in the`
  line `Collector's hands, bar or render void or voidable a sale under this Act, unless such money stand in the`
  line `defaulter's name alone and without dispute, and unless, after application in due time made by the`
  line `defaulter, or after the written agreement provided for in Section XV of this Act, the Collector shall have`
  line `neglected, or refused on insufficient grounds, to transfer it in payment of the arrear of revenue due.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (70806)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Deposits receivable from persons not proprietors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70806&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Collector or other Officer as aforesaid`
  line `shall, at any time before sunset of the latest day of payment determined according to Section III of this`
  line `Act, receive as a deposit from any person not being a proprietor of the estate or share of an estate in`
  line `arrear, the amount of the arrear of revenue due, to be credited in payment of the arrear at sunset as`
  line `aforesaid, unless before that time the arrear shall have been paid by a defaulting proprietor of the estate.`
  line `And in case the person so depositing, whose money shall have been credited in the manner aforesaid,`
  line `shall be a party in a suit pending before a Court of Justice for the possession of the estate or share from`
  line `which the arrear is due, or any part thereof, it shall be competent to the said Court to order the said party`
  line `to be put into temporary possession of the said estate or share or part thereof, subject to the rules in force`
  line `for taking security in the cases of parties in Civil suits. And if the person so depositing, whose money`
  line `shall have been credited as aforesaid, shall prove before a competent Civil Court that the deposit was`
  line `made in order to protect an interest of the said person, which would have been endangered or damaged by`
  line `the sale, or which he believed in good faith would have been endangered or damaged by the sale, he shall`
  line `be entitled to recover the amount of the deposit, with or without interest as the Court may determine, from`
  line `the defaulting proprietor, And if the party so depositing, whose money shall have been credited as`
  line `aforesaid, shall prove before such a Court that the deposit was necessary in order to protect any lien he`
  line `had on the estate or share or part thereof, the amount so credited shall be added to the amount of the`
  line `original lien.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (70807)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Separation of shares held in common, by the opening of a separate account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70807&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When a recorded`
  line `sharer of a joint estate, held in common tenancy, desires to pay his shares of the government revenue`
  line `separately, he may submit to the Collector a written application to that effect. The application must`
  line `contain a specification of the share held in the estate by the applicant. The Collector shall then cause to be`
  line `published in his own Office, in the Court of the Judge, Magistrate (or Join Magistrate, as the case may`
  line `be,) and Moonsiffs, and in the Police Thannahs in whose jurisdiction the estate or any part thereof is`
  line `situated, as well as on some conspicuous part of the estate itself, a copy of the application made to him. If,`
  line `within six weeks from the date of the publication of these notices, no objection is made by any other`
  line `recorded sharer, the Collector shall open a separate account with the applicant, and shall credit separately`
  line `to his share all payments made by him on account of it. The date on which the collector his sanction to the`
  line `opening of a separate account, shall be held to be that from which the separate liabilities of the share of`
  line `the applicant commence`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (70861)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Separation of shares consisting of specific portions of land, by the opening of a separate account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70861&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `When a recorded sharer of a joint estate, whose share consists of a specific portion of the land`
  line `of the estate, desires to pay his share of the Government revenue separately, he may submit to the`
  line `Collector a written application to that effect. The application must contain a specification of the land`
  line `comprised in his share, and of the boundaries and extent thereof, together with a statement of the amount`
  line `of sudder jumma heretofore paid on account of it. On the receipt of this application, the Collector shall`
  line `cause it to be published ill the manner prescribed for publication of notice in the last preceding Section. In`
  line `the event of no objection being urged by any recorded co-sharer within six weeks from the time of`
  line `publication, the Collector shall open a separate account with the applicant, and shall credit separately to`
  line `his share all payments made by him on account of it. The date on which the Collector records his sanction to the opening of a separate account, shall be held to be that from which the separate liabilities of the`
  line `share of the applicant commence.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (70809)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `If objection be made, parties to be referred to the Civil Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70809&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `If any recorded proprietor of`
  line `the estate, whether the same be held in common tenancy or otherwise, object that the applicant has no`
  line `right to the share claimed by him, or that his interest in the estate is less or other than that claimed by him,`
  line `or if the application be in respect of a specific portion of the land of an estate, that the amount of sudder`
  line `jumma stated by the applicant to have been heretofore paid on account of such portion of land, is not the`
  line `amount which has been recognized by the other sharers as the jumma thereof, the Collector shall refer the`
  line `parties to the Civil Court, and shall suspend proceedings until the question at issue is judicially`
  line determined.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (70810)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Sale of separate shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70810&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Collector shall have ordered a separate account or`
  line `accounts to be kept for one or more shares, if the estate shall become liable to sale for arrears of revenue,`
  line `the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid in the first place shall put up to sale only that share or those`
  line `shares of the estate from which, according to the separate accounts, an arrear of revenue may be due. In`
  line `all such cases notice of the intention of excluding the share or shares from which no arrear is due shall be`
  line `given in the advertisement of sale prescribed in Section VI of this Act. The share or shares sold, together`
  line `with the share or shares excluded from the sale, shall continue to constitute one integral estate, the share`
  line `or shares sold being charged with the separate portion or the aggregate of the several separate portions of`
  line `jumma assigned thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (70811)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Entire estate may be sold under certain conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70811&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If in any case of sale held according to`
  line `the provisions of the last preceding Section, the highest offer for the share exposed to sale shall not equal`
  line `the amount of arrear due thereupon to the date of sale the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid shall stop`
  line `the sale, and shall declare that the entire estate will be put up to sale for arrear of revenue at a future`
  line `date, unless the other recorded sharer or sharers, or one or more of them, shall within ten days purchase`
  line `the share in arrear by paying to Government the whole arrear due from such share. If such purchase be`
  line `completed, the collector or other officer as aforesaid shall give such certificate and delivery of possession`
  line `as are provided for in Sections XXVIII and XXIX of this Act, to the purchaser or purchasers, who shall`
  line `have the same rights as if the share had been purchased by him or them at the sale. If no such purchase be`
  line `made within ten days as aforesaid, the entire estate shall be sold, after notification for such period and`
  line `publication in such manner as if proscribed in Section VI of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (70812)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Deposit for the protection of an estate from sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70812&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If any recorded proprietor or co-partner of`
  line `an estate shall deposit with the Collector money, or Government securities, endorsed and made payable to`
  line `the order of the Collector, and shall sign an agreement pledging the same to Government by way of`
  line `security for the jumma of the entire estate and authorizing the Collector to apply to the payment of any`
  line `arrear of revenue that may become due from that estate the whole or any portion of the said money or`
  line `securities that may be necessary for that purpose, then in the case of any arrear of revenue due from the`
  line `said estate not being paid before sunset of the latest day of payment fixed under III of this Act, the`
  line `Collector shall apply to the payment of such arrear the said money or securities, as may be necessary ; and`
  line `for this purpose the Collector shall first apply any money that may be in his hands and any interest that`
  line `may be due upon such securities, and may then sell and transfer the securities, for any balance that may`
  line `remain, And so long as any money or securities as aforesaid, sufficient to cover any arrear that may fall`
  line `due, shall remain and he available as aforesaid, the estate for the protection of which the said deposit was`
  line `made shall be exempted from sale for arrears of revenue. All monies and securities so deposited shall be`
  line `exempt from attachment otherwise than in execution of a decree of a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (70813)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Withdrawal of the deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70813&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `It shall be competent to the person making a deposit under the`
  line `provision of the last preceding Section, or his representative or assignee, at any time to withdraw the`
  line `deposit and to revoke the pledge of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (70814)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Estates under Court of Wards or attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70814&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No estate shall be liable to sale for the`
  line `recovery of arrears which have accrued during the period of its being. under the of the Court`
  line `of Wards; and no estate the sole property of a minor or minors and descended to him or them by the`
  line `regular course of inheritance duly notified to the Collector for the information of the Court of Wards, but`
  line `of which .the Court of Wards has not assumed the management under Regulation VI. 1822, shall be sold`
  line `for arrears of revenue accruing subsequently to his or their succession to the same, until the minor or`
  line `minors, or one of them, shall have attained the full age of eighteen years. And no estate held under`
  line `attachment by the revenue authorities otherwise than by order of a judicial authority, shall be liable to sale`
  line `for arrears accruing whilst it was so held under attachment. And no estate held under attachment or`
  line `managed by a Revenue Officer, in pursuance of an order of a judicial authority, shall be liable to sale for`
  line `the recovery of arrears of revenue accruing during the period of such attachment or management until`
  line `after the end of the year in which such arrears accrued.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (70815)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Estates may be specially exempted from sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70815&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `It shall be competent to the Collector or`
  line `other Officer as aforesaid, at any time before the sale of an estate or share of an estate shall have`
  line `commenced, to exempt such estate or share from sale ; and in like manner it shall be competent to the`
  line `Commissioner of Revenue, at any time before the sale of an estate or share of an estate shall have`
  line `commenced, to exempt such estate or share from sale, by a special order to the Collector or other Officer`
  line `as aforesaid to that effect in each case; and no such sale shall be legal if held after the receipt of such`
  line `order of exemption.`
  line
  line `Proviso.--Provided, however, and it is hereby enacted, that the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid`
  line `or the Commissioner shall duly record in a proceeding the teas on for granting such exemption ; provided also that an order for exemption so issued by the Commissioner shall not affect the legality of a`
  line `sale which may have taken place before the receipt by the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid of the`
  line `order of exemption.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (70816)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Sales where to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70816&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Sales shall ordinarily be made by the Collector or other Officer as`
  line `aforesaid in the land revenue Office at the Sudder Station of the District: provided, however, that it shal1`
  line `be competent to the Board of Revenue to prescribe a place for holding sales other than such Office`
  line `whenever they shall consider it beneficial to the parties concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (70817)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Adjournment of sales.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70817&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `In case the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid shall be unable from`
  line `Sickness, from occurrence of a holiday, or from any other cause, to commence the sale on the day of sale`
  line `fixed as aforesaid ; or if, having commenced it, he be unable, from any cause, to`
  line `complete it; he shall be competent to adjourn it to the next day following, not being Sunday or other close`
  line `holiday, recording his reasons for such adjournment, forwarding a copy of such record to the`
  line `Commissioner of Revenue, and announcing the adjournment by a written proclamation stuck up in his`
  line `cutcherry ; and so on, from day to day, until he shall be able to commence upon, or to complete the sale;`
  line `but, with the exception of adjournments so made, recorded, and reported, each sale shall invariably be`
  line `made on the day of sale fixed in the manner aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (70818)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Order of selling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70818&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `On the day of sale fixed according to Section VI of this Act sales shall`
  line `proceed in regular order ; the estate to be sold bearing the lowest number on the towjee or register in use`
  line `in the Collector’s Office of the district being put up first, and so on, in regular sequence; and it shall not`
  line `be lawful for the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid to put up any estate out of its regular order by`
  line `number, except where it may be necessary to do so 011 default of deposit, as provided in Section XXII of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (70819)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Deposit on account of purchase money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70819&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The party who shall be declared the purchaser of an`
  line `estate or share of an estate at any such public sale as aforesaid, shall be required to deposit or`
  line `immediately or as soon after the conclusion of the sale of the estate at share as the Collector or other`
  line `Officer as aforesaid may think necessary, either in cash Bank of Bengal Notes or Post Bills or`
  line `Government Securities to be valued at the market rate of the day, duly endorsed, twenty percent on the amount of his bid and in default of such deposit, the estate or share shall forthwith be put up again and`
  line sold.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (70820)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Full payment of purchase money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70820&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The full amount of purchase money shall be made good`
  line `by the purchaser before sunset of the thirtieth day from that on which the sale of the estate or share of all`
  line `estate bought by him took place, reckoning that day as one of the thirty ; or if the thirtieth day be a`
  line `Sunday Or other close holiday, then on the first office day after the thirtieth: and in default of payment`
  line `within the prescribed period as aforesaid, the deposit shall be forfeited to Government, the estate or share`
  line `shall be resold, and the defaulting purchaser shall forfeit all claim to the estate or share, or to any part of`
  line `the sum for which it may subsequently be sold. And in the event of the proceeds of the sale which may be`
  line `eventually consummated being less than the price bid by the defaulting bidder aforesaid, the difference`
  line `shall be leviable from him by any process authorized for realizing an arrear of public revenue, and such`
  line `difference shall be considered to be a part of the purchase money and shall be dealt with in the manner`
  line `hereinafter prescribe for the disposal thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (70821)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Re-sale.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70821&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `When default is made in the payment of purchase money a notification of the`
  line `intended re-sale shall be published for the period and in the manner prescribed in Section VI of this Act,`
  line `but such notification shall not be published until the expiration of three clear days after the day on which`
  line `the default shall have occurred ; and if the Payment or tender of payment of the arrear on account of`
  line `which the estate or share was first sold, and of any arrear which may have subsequently become : due`
  line `shall be made by or on behalf of the proprietor of the estate or share before sunset of the third day, the`
  line `issue of the notification of re-sale shall be stayed. The rules contained in the last preceding Section shall`
  line `be applicable to every such re-sale. Provided that if default of payment of purchase money shall occur`
  line `more than once, the amount to be recovered from the defaulting bidders shall be the difference between`
  line `the highest bid and the proceeds of the sale eventually consummated, which amount may be levied in`
  line `manner aforesaid from any of the defaulting bidders to the extent of the amount by which his bid exceeds`
  line `the amount realized.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (70822)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70822&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the Commissioner of Revenue to receive an appeal against may`
  line `sale made under this Act, if preferred to him on or before the fifteenth day from the date of sale,`
  line `reckoning as in Section XXIII, or if preferred to the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid for`
  line `transmission to the Commissioner, on or before the tenth day from the day of sale, and not`
  line `otherwise; and the Commissioner shall be competent in every case of appeal so preferred to annul any`
  line `sale of an estate or share of an estate made under this Act, which shall appear to him not to have been`
  line `conducted according to the provisions of this Act, awarding at compensation for his loss, if the sale shall`
  line `have been occasioned by neglect of the proprietor, such compensation not to exceed the interest, at the`
  line `highest rate of the current Government Securities of its being retained in the Collector’s Office ; and the`
  line `order of the Commissioner shall in such cases be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (70823)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Annulment of sale in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70823&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `It shall be competent to the Commissioner of Revenue,`
  line `on the ground of hardship or injustice, to suspend the passing of final orders in any case of appeal from a`
  line `sale, and to represent the case to the Board of Revenue, who, if they see cause, may recommend to the`
  line `local Government to annul the sale ; and the local Government in any such case may annul the sale and`
  line `cause the estate or share of an estate to be restored to the proprietor on such conditions as may appear`
  line `equitable and proper.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (70824)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Sales when final.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70824&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `All sales of which the purchase money has been paid up as prescribed in`
  line `Section XXIII of this Act, and against which no appeal shall have been preferred, shall be final and`
  line `conclusive at noon of the thirtieth day from the day of sale, reckoning the said day of sale as the first of`
  line `the said thirty days. And sales against which all appeal may have been preferred, and dismissed by the`
  line `Commissioner, shall be final and conclusive from the date of such dismissal, if more than thirty days from`
  line `the day of sale, or if less, then at noon of the thirtieth day as above provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (70825)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Certificate of sales.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70825&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Immediately upon a sale becoming final and conclusive, the Collector`
  line `or other Officer as aforesaid shall give to the purchaser a certificate of title in the form prescribed in`
  line `Schedule A annexed to this Act. And the said certificate shall be deemed in any Court of Justice sufficient`
  line `evidence of the title to the estate or share of an estate sold being vested in the person or persons named`
  line `from the date specified ; and the Collector shall also notify such transfer by written proclamation in his`
  line `own Officer and in the Courts of the Moonsiffs and Police Thannahs within whose jurisdiction any part of`
  line `the estate or share sold shall be situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (70826)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Delivery of possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70826&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Collector or other Officer as aforesaid shall order delivery of`
  line `possession of the estate or share purchased to be made by removing any person who may refuse to vacate`
  line `the same, and by proclamation to the occupants of the property by beat of drum or in such other mode as`
  line `may be customary, at some convenient place or places; and by affixing a copy of the certificate at the`
  line `Mal cutchery or in some conspicuous place of the estate or share of an estate purchased.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (70827)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Liability of purchaser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70827&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The party certified as the proprietor of an estate or share of an estate`
  line `by purchase under this Act, shall be answerable for all instalments of the revenue of Government which`
  line `may fall due after the latest day of payment aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (70828)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Application of purchase money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70828&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Collector shall apply the purchase money first to the`
  line `liquidation of all arrears due upon the latest day of payment from the estate or share of an estate sold; and`
  line `secondly to the liquidation of all outstanding demands debited to the estate or share of an estate in the`
  line `public accounts of the District; holding the residue, if any, in deposit on account of the late recorded`
  line `proprietor or proprietors of the estate share of an estate sold or their heirs or representatives to be paid to`
  line `his or their receipt on demand in the manner following : to wit, in shares proportioned to their recorded`
  line `interest in the estate or share of an estate sold, if such distinction of shares were recorded, or if not, then`
  line `as an aggregate sum to the whole body of proprietors upon their joint receipt. And if before payment to`
  line `the late proprietor or proprietors of any surplus that may remain of the purchase money, the same be`
  line `claimed by any creditor in satisfaction of a debt, such surplus shall not be payable to such claimant, nor`
  line `shall it be withheld from the proprietor, except under precept of a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (70829)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Notification of annulment of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70829&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The annulment by a Commissioner or by Government`
  line `of a sale made under this Act shall be publicly notified by the Collector or other Officer as aforesaid, in`
  line `the same manner as the becoming final and conclusive of sales is required to be notified by Section`
  line `XXVIII of this Act; and the amount of deposit and balance of purchase money shall be forthwith returned`
  line `to the purchaser with interest thereon at the highest rates of the current public Securities; which shall be`
  line `paid by the Government, unless the proprietor shall have become liable for the same under the provisions`
  line `of Section XXV or Section XXVI of this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (70830)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Jurisdiction of Civil Courts in suits to annul sales.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70830&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No sale for arrears of revenue or`
  line `other demands realizable in the same manner as arrears of revenue are realizable made after the passing of`
  line `this Act, shall be annulled by a Court of Justice, except upon the ground of its having been made contrary`
  line `to the provisions of this Act, and then only on proof that the plaintiff has sustained substantial injury by`
  line `reason of the irregularity complained of: and no such sale shall be annulled upon such ground, unless such`
  line `ground shall have been declared and specified in an appeal made to the Commissioner under Section`
  line `XXV of this Act: and no suit to annul a sale made under this Act shall be received by any Court of Justice`
  line `unless it shall be instituted within one year from the date of the sale becoming final and conclusive as`
  line `provided in Section XXVII of this Act: and no person shall be entitled to contest the legality of a sale,`
  line `after having received any portion of the purchase money.`
  line
  line `Proviso.--Provided, however, that nothing in this Act contained shall be construed to debar any`
  line `person considering himself wronged by any act or omission connected with a sale under this Act, from his`
  line `remedy in a personal action for damages against the person by whose act or omission he considers`
  line `himself to have been wronged.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (70831)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Effects of annulment by decree of Court of sales under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70831&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `If a sale made under`
  line `this Act be annulled by a final decree of a Civil Court application for the execution of such decree shall be`
  line `made within six months after the date thereof, otherwise the party in whose favor such decree was passed`
  line `shall lose all benefit therefrom. And no order for restoring such decreeholder to possession shall be`
  line `passed until any amount of surplus purchase money that may have been paid away by order of a Civil`
  line `Court be repaid by him, with interest at the highest rate of the current Government Securities. And if such`
  line `party shall neglect to pay any amount so recoverable, within six months from the date of such final`
  line `decree, he shall lose all benefit therefrom.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (70832)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `If sale annulled purchase money to be refunded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70832&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `In the event of a sale being annulled by`
  line `a final decree of a Court of Justice, and the former proprietor being restored to possession, the purchase`
  line `money shall be refunded to the purchaser by Government, together with interest at the highest rate of the`
  line `current public securities.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (70862)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Suit brought to oust a purchaser on the ground that the purchase was made for another person, to be dismissen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70862&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any suit brought to oust the certified purchaser as aforesaid on the ground`
  line `that the purchase was made on behalf of another person not the certified purchaser, or on behalf partly of`
  line `himself and partly of another person, though by agreement the name of the certified purchaser was used,`
  line `shall be dismissed with costs.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (70834)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Rights of a purchaser of a permanently settled estate sold for its own arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70834&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The purchaser .of an entire estate in the permanently settled Districts of Bengal, Behar, and`
  line `Orissa, sold under this Act for the recovery of arrears due on account of the same, shall acquire the estate`
  line `free from all encumbrances which may have been imposed upon it after the time of settlement; and shall`
  line `be entitled to avoid and annul all under-tenures and forthwith to eject all undertenants, with the following`
  line `exceptions:`
  line
  line `First. Istemraree or mokurreree tenures which have been held at a fixed rent from the time of the`
  line `permanent settlement.`
  line
  line `Secondly. Tenures existing at the time of settlement, which have not been held at a fixed rent.`
  line `Provided always that the rents of such tenures shall be liable to enhancement under any law for the time`
  line `being in force for the enhancement of the rent of such tenures.`
  line
  line `Thirdly. Talookdaree and other similar tenures created since the time of settlement and held`
  line `immediately of the proprietors of estates, and farms for terms of years so held, when such tenures and`
  line `farms have been duly registered under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `Fourthly. Leases of lands whereon dwelling houses, manufactories, or other permanent buildings have`
  line `been erected, or whereon gardens, plantations, tanks, wells, canals, places of worship, or burning or`
  line `burying grounds have been made, or wherein mines have been sunk.`
  line
  line `And such a purchaser as is aforesaid shall be entitled to proceed in the manner prescribed by any law`
  line `for the time being in force for the enhancement of the rent of any land coming within the fourth class of`
  line `exceptions above made, if he can prove the same to have been held at what was originally an unfair rent,`
  line `and if the same shall not have been held at a fixed rent, equal to the rent of good arable land, for a term`
  line `exceeding twelve years; but not otherwise.`
  line
  line `Proviso.---Provided always that nothing in this Section contained shall be construed to entitle any`
  line `such purchaser as aforesaid to eject any ryot having a right of occupancy at a fixed rent or at a rent`
  line `assessable according to fixed rules under the laws in force, or to enhance the rent of any such ryot`
  line `otherwise than in the manner prescribed by such laws, or otherwise than the former proprietor,`
  line `irrespectively of all engagements made since the time of settlement, may have been entitled to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (70835)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Registration of talookdaree tenurs created after settlement and held for terms of years.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70835&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The following rules for the registration of talookdaree and other similar tenure created since the`
  line `time of settlement, and held immediately of the proprietors of estates, and of farms for terms of years so`
  line `held, shall be observed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (70836)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Common and special registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70836&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `There shall be two sets of registers, one for common`
  line `registry and one for special registry. Common registry shall secure such tenures and farms against any`
  line `auction purchaser at a sale for arrears of revenue except the Government. Special registry shall secure`
  line `such tenures and farms against any auction purchaser at a sale for arrears of revenue including the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (70837)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Application for registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70837&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The holder of any talookdaree, other similar tenure, such as is`
  line `described in Section XXXVIII of this Act, desirous of registering it, shall apply by petition to the`
  line `Collector of the District to which the estate belongs. The application shall state when description of`
  line `registry is desired, and shall contain the following particulars so far as the same are ascertainable:`
  line
  line `1. The Pergunnah or pergunnahs in which the tenure is situated.`
  line
  line `2. The nature of tenure.`
  line
  line `3. The name or names of the billage or villages whereof the land is composed, or wherein it is`
  line situated.
  line
  line `4. The area of the land comprised in the tenure, with its boundaries in complete detail.`
  line
  line `5. The amount of rent payable annually for the tenure, and whether the rent is fixed for a rent of`
  line `years or in perpetuity, and the duties, if any, required to be performed on account of it.`
  line
  line `6. The date of the deed constituting the tenure, or the date when the tenure was created.`
  line
  line `7. The name of the proprietor who created the tenure.`
  line
  line `8. The name of the original holder of the tenure.`
  line
  line `9. The name of the present possessor, and if he be not the original holder, the mode in which he`
  line `succeeded to the tenure, whether by inheritance, gift, purchase, or otherwise, and whether he holds`
  line `jointly or solely.`
  line
  line `Holders of such farms as are described in the said Section may apply in like manner for registry of`
  line `the same. The application shall contain such of the foregoing particulars as are applicable to farms.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (70838)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Procedure on application for common registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70838&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `When the application is for common`
  line `registry, the Collector shall serve a notice on the recorded proprietor or proprietors of the estate in which`
  line `the tenure or farm is situated, or the authorized agent of such proprietor or proprietors, with a copy of the`
  line `application annexed; and shall cause a notice, with a copy of the application annexed, to be affixed in his`
  line `Office, and at the malcutcherry of the estate in which the tenure or farm is situated, or in such other place`
  line `or places as in the opinion of the Collector may be best suited to give publicity to the application,`
  line `requiring the proprietor or any party interested, within thirty days from the issue of the said notice, to file`
  line `any objections he may have to the registry of the tenure or farm, or to any statement contained in the`
  line `application. If within the limited time no objection is made, the Collector shall register the tenure or farm.`
  line `If within the limited time an objection is made any recorded proprietor, or by any party interested not`
  line `being a proprietor, the Collector shall examine the person so objecting or his authorized agent, and if it`
  line `shall appear to him that such person has probable, ground of objection, the Collector shall suspend`
  line `proceedings, and shall refer the parties to the Civil Court: otherwise he shall grant the application. If the`
  line `decision of the Civil Court be in favor of the applicant, the Collector, on the presentation of a copy of the`
  line `final decree, shall register the tenure or farm.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (70839)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Procedure on application for special registry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70839&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `When the application is for special registry,`
  line `the Collector shall serve and issue the notices prescribed in the last proceeding Section. If within the`
  line `limited time no objection is made, the Collector shall cause any enquiry that he may deem necessary for`
  line `the security of the Government revenue, to be made ; and if he is satisfied that the Government revenue of`
  line `the parent estate is sufficient secured so far as it may be affected by the tenure or farm in question, he`
  line `shall report the case to the commissioner, who, if also satisfied on that point, shall direct the tenure or`
  line `farm to be registered according to the application; otherwise the application shall be rejected. If within the`
  line `limited time any recorded proprietor or any party interested not being a proprietor object to the registry,`
  line `the Collector shall examine the person so objecting or his authorized agent, and if it shall appear to him`
  line `that such person has probable ground of objection, shall suspend proceedings, and shall refer the parties to`
  line `the Civil Court; otherwise he shall proceed as if no objection had been made. If the decision of the Civil`
  line `Court be in favor of the applicant, the Collector, on the presentation of a copy of the final decree, shall`
  line `proceed as above provided for cases in which no objection is made within the limited time.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (70840)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Registration of leases of certain lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70840&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Leases of lands of the description specified in the`
  line `fourth exceptional class in Section XXXVII, may be registered, at the option of the holders, in the manner`
  line `and under the rules hereinbefore provided for the registry of Talookdaree and other similar tenures.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (70841)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Registration of old tenures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70841&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Tenures of the first and second exceptional classes in Section`
  line `XXXVII may be registered, at the option of the holders; and when so registered shall be entered only in`
  line `the special register. Application for such registry shall contain the particulars specified in Section XL so`
  line `far as the same are ascertainable, and notices shall be served and issued in the manner prescribed in`
  line `Section XLI. If within the limited time no objection is made by any recorded proprietor or by any party`
  line `interested not being a proprietor, the Collector shall make such enquiries as may be necessary to satisfied`
  line `him as to the validity of the tenure; and if the result be to satisfy him that the tenure is valid, he shall`
  line `report the case to the Commissioner, who, if also satisfied that the tenure is valid, shall direct it to be`
  line `entered in the special register; otherwise the application for registry shall be rejected. If within the limited`
  line `time any recorded proprietor or other party as aforesaid object to the registry of the tenure, the Collector`
  line `shall examine the person so objecting of' his authorized agent, and if it shall appear to him that such`
  line `person has probable ground of objection, shall suspend proceedings, and refer the parties to the Civil`
  line `Court; otherwise he shall proceed as if no objection had been made. If the decision of the Civil Court be`
  line `in favor of the applicant, the Collector, on the presentation of a copy of the final decree, shall proceed as`
  line `above provided for cases in which no objection is made within the limited time.`
  line
  line `Proviso.—Provided always that nothing contained in this Section shall be understood as rendering`
  line `registration necessary for the protection of bond fide tenures of the description herein referred to.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (70842)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Time for application for registry of tenures and farms.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70842&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Application for registry existing`
  line `tenures and farms must be made within three years after the passing of this Act Application for the`
  line `registry of tenures created after the passing of this Act must be made within three months from the date of`
  line `the deed constituting the tenure.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (70843)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Expenses of measurement, survey, or local enquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70843&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The actual expenses of any`
  line `measurement, survey, or local enquiry made under Sections XLII and XLIV of this Act, shall be borne by`
  line `the party who applies for the registry of his tenure or farm; and such party may be required by the`
  line `Collector from time to time to make such advances on this account as he may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (70844)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Civil Court not competent to order entry in the special register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70844&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The actual expenses of any`
  line `measurement, survey, or local enquiry made under Sections XLII and XLIV of this Act, shall be borne by`
  line `the party who applies for the registry of his tenure or farm; and such party may be required by the`
  line `Collector from time to time to make such advances on this account as he may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (70845)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Suit for the cancelment of the registry of a tenure or farm.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70845&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the general law`
  line `of limitation, any person thinking himself wronged by the registry of a tenure or farm, may file a suit for`
  line `the cancelment of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (70846)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Proceedings of Revenue Authorities in the registration of tenures, &c.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70846&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `In the execution of`
  line `their functions in the registration of tenures and farms under this Act, all subordinate Revenue Authorities`
  line `shall proceed in accordance with the general instructions which they may receive from the superior`
  line `Revenue Authorities to whom they are subordinate, and from the local Government; and all orders passed`
  line `under the Sections aforesaid shall be open to appeal in usual course. The order of a Commissioner for the`
  line `special registry of a tenure under the provisions of this Act, shall be open at any time within one year`
  line `from the date of registry to revision by the Board of Revenue or the local Government, on the ground of`
  line `the Government Revenue not having been sufficiently secured or of the invalidity of the tenure, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (70847)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Effect of entry in the special register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70847&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Entry in the special register shall be an effectual`
  line `protection of the tenure or farm so registered, unless in a suit instituted by Government in a Civil Court`
  line `within the period allowed for suits for the recovery of the public revenue a decree be passed pronouncing`
  line `the registration to have been obtained by fraud, to the injury of the Government revenue. Provided that a`
  line `tenure or farm in the hands of a bond fide purchaser for value shall not be avoided by reason of such`
  line `fraud. But the tenure or farm shall be liable to such amount of rent as would have been fair and equitable`
  line `at the time of the special registry thereof, such amount to be fixed by the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (70863)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Protection of talookdaree tenures pending enquity, in case of sale of parent estate for arrears of revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70863&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Tenures and farms of the third exceptional class described in Section XXXVII of this Act,`
  line `for the special registration of which application shall be made within the prescribed time, and in respect of`
  line `which the Collector shall have commenced the enquiry prescribed in Section XLII, shall, in case of the`
  line `sale of the parent estate for arrears of revenue, be protected pending the duration of such enquiry, and`
  line `shall be protected eventually by registration, if the final award of the Revenue Authorities, upon such`
  line `application, be in favor of the claimant.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (70849)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Rights of a purchaser of an estate not permanently settled sold for its own arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70849&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The purchaser of an estate in a district not permanently settled, sold under this Act for the`
  line `recovery of arrears due on account of the same, shall acquire the estate free from all encumbrances which`
  line `may have been imposed upon it after the time of settlement, and shall be entitled to avoid and annul all`
  line `tenures which may have originated with the defaulter or his predecessors, being representatives or`
  line `assignees of the original engager, as well as all agreements with ryots or the like settled or accredited by`
  line `the first engager or his representatives, subsequently to the last settlement, as well as all tenures which the`
  line `first engager may, under the conditions of his settlement, have been competent to set aside, alter, or`
  line `renew, saving always and except leases of lands whereon dwelling houses, manufactories, or other`
  line `permanent buildings have been erected, or whereon gardens, plantations, tanks, wells, canals, places of`
  line `worship, or burning or burying grounds have been made, wherein mines have been sunk, which leases or`
  line `engagements shall, so as the land is duly appropriated to such purposes, and the stipulated rent paid,`
  line `continue in force and effect. Provided that nothing contained in this Section shall be construed to entitle`
  line `any purchaser of land at a public sale for arrears of revenue to demand a higher rate of rent from any`
  line `persons whose tenure or agreement may be annulled as aforesaid, than was demandable by the cases in`
  line `which such persons may have held their lands under engagements, stipulating for a lower rate of rent than`
  line `would have been justly demandable for the land, or in cases in which it may be proved that, according to`
  line `the custom of the pergunnah, mouzah, or other local division, such persons are liable to be called upon for`
  line `any new assessment, or other demand not interdicted by the regulations of Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (70850)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Rights of a purchaser being a sharer in any estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70850&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Excepting sharers in estates under`
  line `butwarrah who may have saved their shares from sale under Sections XXXIII and XXXIV Regulation`
  line `XIX. 1814, and sharers with whom the Collector, under Sections X and Xl of this Act, has opened separate accounts, any recorded or unrecorded proprietor or co-partner, who may purchase the estate of`
  line `which he is proprietor or co-partner; or who by re-purchase or otherwise may recover possession of the`
  line `said estate, after it has been sold for arrears under this Act; and likewise any purchaser of an estate sold`
  line `for arrears or demands other than those accruing upon itself; shall by such purchase acquire the estate`
  line `subject to all its encumbrances existing at the time of sale and shall not acquire any rights in respect to`
  line `under-tenants or ryots, with were not possessed by the previous proprietor at the time of the sale of the`
  line `said estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (70851)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Rights of purchasers of shares of estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70851&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `When a share or shares of an estate may be sold`
  line `under the provisions of Section XIII or Section XIV, the purchaser shall acquire the share or shares`
  line `subject to all encumbrances, and shall not acquire any rights which were not possessed by the previous`
  line `owner or owners.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (70852)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Recovery of arrears due to defaulters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70852&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Arrears of rent which on the latest day of payment may`
  line `be due to the defaulter from his under-tenants or ryots, shall, in the event of a sale, be recoverable by him`
  line `after the said latest day, by any process except distraint which might have been used by him for that`
  line `purpose on or before the said latest day.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (70853)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Punishment for contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70853&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Any Collector or other Officer as aforesaid conducting a sale`
  line `under this Act shall be competent to punish any contempt committed in his presence in open cutcherry or`
  line `office for the time being, by fine, to an extent not exceeding two hundred Rupees, commutable, if not`
  line `paid, to imprisonment in the Civil jail for a period not exceeding one month; and the Magistrate to whom`
  line `such an offender may be sent by a Collector or other Officer as aforesaid, shall carry his sentence into`
  line `effect. Provided that an appeal from any order passed under this Section shall lie to the Revenue`
  line `Commissioner, whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (70854)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Default in making deposit to be considered a contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70854&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `A default to make good a bid by`
  line `making the deposit required by Section XXII of this Act, shall be held to be a contempt.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (70855)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Government may purchase at a sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70855&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `When an estate is put up for sale under this Act for`
  line `the recovery of arrears of revenue due thereon, if there be no bid, the Collector or other Officer as`
  line `aforesaid may purchase the estate on account of the Government for one Rupee, or if the highest bid be`
  line `insufficient to cover the said arrears and those subsequently accruing up to the date of sale, the Collector`
  line `or other Officer as aforesaid may take or purchase the estate on account of the Government at the highest`
  line `amount bid; in both which cases the Government shall acquire the property subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (70856)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Fees and charges demandable by Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70856&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The Collector on the part of the Government`
  line `shall be entitled to demand from applicants under Sections X and XI, Sections XV and XVI, and Sections`
  line `XL, XLIII, and XLIV of this Act, fees not exceeding the rates specified in Schedule B to this Act`
  line `annexed, which schedule shall be taken as part of this Act; and applications under the said Sections shall`
  line `not be received unless the said fees are tendered therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (70857)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Regulations VII. 1822 and IX. 1825 to be in force in certain estates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70857&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of`
  line `Regulation VII, 1822 and Regulation IX. 1825 shall be in force in every estate in any part of which a`
  line `measurement, survey, or local enquiry may be made under this Act; and in every estate purchased or`
  line `taken on account of Government under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (70858)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70858&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `In the construction of this Act the word “Collector” shall include a Deputy`
  line `Collector or other Officer exercising by the authority of Government the powers of a Collector or deputy`
  line Collector.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (70859)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Application and commencement of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098&sectionId=70859&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_185911_1667972824098
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `The operation of this Act shall be confined to such parts of the Lower`
  line `Provinces in the Presidency of Fort William in Bengal as are or shall be subject to the general Regulations`
  line `of that Presidency.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
